<ul><li>It is a relatively easy to&nbsp;<i>understand, debug and maintainble</i>&nbsp;<u>unit of code</u>.</li><li>They can be&nbsp;<b>tested independently</b>.</li><li>A tested subroutine can be&nbsp;<i>reused with confidence</i>.</li><li>In a <b>collaboration</b>, each programmer can be given a&nbsp;<i>specific set of subroutines to work on</i>.</li><li>Large projects become&nbsp;<u>easier to monitor and control</u>.</li></ul>